snippet.textDisplay: Yea I have two Yamaha FXHO's and They are both like this, if you ever have to tow one it is a real pain in the ass! I have been told to tow going 5mph or less! if you are out somewhere a good distance from where you put your skis in, 5mph is forever away. I put a few clamps in my ski so I can clamp off the hose, but not sure if I would remember what hose I need to clamp off. Correct me if I am wrong, but I have herd that some SeaDoo's have pass thru exhaust systems that do not thru the engine but simply pass close enough to drain heat or something. Mostly to help with salt water issues, but I would assume would help with this kind of thing also.
